# ✅ Phase 3: Verification Gate (Quality Assurance)

## 📜 Verification Mission
- Ensure all atomic commits from the execution phase meet quality standards before merging.
- Produce a human-auditable verification report.

## 🧪 1. Automated Checks (Run in sequence)

```bash
# Step V.1 — Type Safety
npx tsc --noEmit

# Step V.2 — Code Quality  
npm run lint

# Step V.3 — Unit Tests (if applicable)
npm test -- --passWithNoTests

# Step V.4 — Build Validation (catch runtime issues)
npm run build
```

For each check, you MUST report:
- ✅ `PASS` with zero warnings, or
- ❌ `FAIL` with the exact error message

**If any check fails:** Stop verification. Fix the failure as a new atomic step under `/e`. Do NOT proceed to deployment.

## 📋 2. Verification Report Format

After all checks pass, produce this summary:

```markdown
## Verification Report — [Task Name]

### Automated Checks
| Check | Result | Details |
|-------|--------|---------|
| TypeScript (tsc) | ✅ PASS | 0 errors |
| Linter (eslint) | ✅ PASS | 0 warnings |
| Unit Tests | ✅ PASS | 12/12 passed |
| Build | ✅ PASS | 1.2MB bundle |

### Changes Summary
- Files modified: [list]
- Total lines changed: [N logic + N UI]
- Commits in this task: [N]

### Manual Verification Required
- [ ] [Describe any UI change the human needs to visually confirm]
- [ ] [Describe any integration point that needs manual testing]

### Ready for merge: ✅ YES / ❌ NO
```

## 🧹 3. Post-Verification Cleanup

When verification passes and human replies `1`:
1. Run the cleanup protocol: `rm research_summary.md implementation_plan.md task.md`
2. Final commit: `chore(cleanup): remove task artifacts from [task-name]`
3. Merge or push to target branch.

## ⌨️ Command: `/v`
- **Action**: Run all verification checks and produce the verification report.
